radiographic_examinations.findings: The appendix is enlarged measuring 12 mm and does not fill with oral contrast. There is mild associated stranding. There is no surrounding free air, free fluid, or evidence of abscess. The bases of the lungs are clear without nodules or consolidation. There is no pleural effusion. The abdominal vasculature is normal in course and caliber. Acute uncomplicated appendicitis without evidence of perforation or abscess.
